G-141 — The 90-Word Motion (Small Ask, Pin-Tight)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: You can move the calendar with ≤90 words and two pins.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One-sentence ask, one-sentence standard, two pins, one-sentence relief text. No adjectives; file as “Short Motion.”
	•	📝 Assignment: Rewrite a one-page motion into a 90-word version with two pins.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Relief: remand 21 days for harm findings (abuse—wrong test). Pins: Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Short + signable outperforms long + loud.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small card with four lines and two pin dots.

⸻

FG-142 — The Standing Snapshot (Injury • Trace • Redress)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Standing fails when the remedy line is fuzzy.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Three rows: Injury (fact pin), Traceability (order pin), Redressability (your order text). Put it up front.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 3-row standing table for your live issue.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Injury—timing loss (Ex A:1); Trace—Dkt 18:2; Redress—remand 21d for findings.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Redressability is the hinge—write the hinge.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Three boxes pointing to a small order strip.

⸻

FG-143 — Quote the Gap, Not the Feeling
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Your best line is the judge’s own omission.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Quote exactly where the court says “not reached” or skips a factor; two pins; propose the instruction.
	•	📝 Assignment: Find and quote one “gap line” with page:line and write the matching instruction.
	•	✅ Model Response: “‘Did not reach harm’ (Dkt 18:2) → remand 21d for findings (a–d).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Their words win your order.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A highlighted “not reached” line feeding a gavel.

⸻

FG-144 — One-Page Cost Table (FRAP/Rule Cite + Receipts)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Cost fights are math with receipts, not prose.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table: Item • Pages/Units • Rate • Total • Rule; attach receipts; trim non-allowables yourself.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 5-row table and add one voluntary trim line.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Appendix 250 pp × $___ = $__ (FRAP 39); Trim: duplicate set.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Own the math; you’ll own the order.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A mini ledger with one clean total.

⸻

FG-145 — The 2-Schedule Menu (10/10/7 or 7/7/3)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Offer two schedules; let the court pick.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Two lines with dates (rolled for weekends) and caps; tiny tick-box order appended.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft both schedules for your matter with a trigger pin.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Trigger: Rule 58 08/15. □ 10/10/7 (O/R/Rep) □ 7/7/3 (O/R/Rep).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Choice accelerates signature.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two date strips with checkboxes.

⸻

FG-146 — One-Screen SoR + Relief (Anchor the Lens)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put Standards and Relief on one screen; make the brief prove it.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: De Novo / Abuse / Clear Error (one line each + cite) above your two-line order; no adjectives.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build the combined SoR+Relief card and paste into your draft.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Abuse: wrong test (cite). Relief: remand 21d for harm findings; 20-min hearing.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Lens first → view follows.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Three lenses stacked above a small order card.

⸻

FG-147 — Bench Clip (Q • Std • 2 Pins • Ask) on a Sticky
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Print the four beats on a sticky; take it to OA.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Question, Standard, Two pins, Ask; ≤40 words; memorize cadence.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write your sticky and rehearse aloud thrice.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Abuse; harm not reached (Dkt 18:2; Tab 3 p.2). Ask: remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Prepared rhythm beats improvisation.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A yellow sticky with four bullet lines.

⸻

FG-148 — Table of Authorities Detox (Only What You Cite)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: TOA is not a bibliography—cut it to what you use.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Remove uncited authorities; keep parentheticals ≤10 words; align TOA order with headings.
	•	📝 Assignment: Delete three uncited cases and trim two parentheticals.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Winter — factor findings required (holding).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: A light TOA reads as disciplined.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A slim TOA page with short parentheticals.

⸻

FG-149 — Caption-Level Ask (Front-Page Remedy)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put your ask near the caption so no one hunts.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: A short, neutral Relief Sought line under the title; mirror the same line at the end.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft one sentence you can paste under the caption today.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Relief: vacate & remand for factor-tied findings within 21 days.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Visibility changes outcomes.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A title block with a small relief ribbon underneath.

⸻

FG-150 — The 72-Hour After-Order Kit
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Put a bad order into a 72-hour playbook: Clarify • Admin Stay • Rehearing plan.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: One-pagers for each: quote the line, two pins, narrow remedy; prepare templates in advance.
	•	📝 Assignment: Assemble your three one-pagers with blanks for dates and pins.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Clarify p.12 n.3 (‘not reached’); stay ¶3 72h (vendor PO Ex A); rehearing on missing harm findings.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Speed + precision beats shock.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Three thin cards labeled Clarify / Stay / Rehearing.
